issing JUnit tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing test dependencies**\\n\\nThe normal scaffold includes AssertJ, which seems fine since the existing tests compile except for the constructor API. It looks like the dependencies are sufficient, as maven-core transitive dependencies cover all necessary aspects. I’m not using Docker here, but I might want to set \\\"maven.repo.local\\\" to a temporary directory to avoid affecting the CI state when invoking operations. I should consider researching documentation with curl, and I need to ensure that my outputs are valid JSON only. I'll have to keep that in mind.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yYX5xsEjADxOson9ipJUDS0x|fc_0f58cf604103cdce016a409d305c1481979fb421aa2691d1f2", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\nbase='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/maven/2.0.7/maven-2.0.7.pom'\ntext=urllib.request.urlopen(base, timeout=20).read().decode()\nprint(text[:5000])\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1040, "output": 619, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 18555, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782619428886, "responseId": "resp_0f58cf604103cdce016a409d253cec819799c88653d7af6766"}}
